##Two "tangles" in Wuhan

Micro-signal Zhenghedao

Features introduced by Zhenghe Island, a high-end social networking platform focused on entrepreneurs.

During the special period, Wuhan has become a city where people all over the country are concerned and pray for good fortune. What was the real life of the people of Wuhan after the city closure?

Zhenghe island has launched a special column, "Ye Qing: My n day in Wuhan Epidemic Area" , since January 26. Ye Qing, a resident of Wuhan for 40 years, is a scholar and official. For a period of time, he would write down his own experiences and observations of Wuhan, and he would go out to the streets and supermarkets to get first-hand information.

This will be a valuable piece of historical material. Thanks to him, we can feel the Wuhan epidemic more vividly. Let's Cheer for Wuhan Together!

I hope this is the peak

January 29, the fifth day of the first lunar month, Wuhan is still sunny, but the news from Wuhan is not good. My heart is heavy too.

At 2400 hours on January 29,31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 1,737 new cases (the first confirmed case in Tibet) , 131 new severe cases, and 38 new deaths (37 in Hubei and 1 in Sichuan) , there were 21 new cured cases and 4148 suspected cases.

As of 2400 hours on January 29,31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have reported a total of 7,711 confirmed cases, 1,370 severe cases and 170 cumulative deaths, a total of 124 patients were cured and 12167 suspected cases were found.

Between 00:00 and 24:00 on the 29th, there were 1,032 new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Hubei Province (including 356 in Wuhan) . There were 37 new deaths in the province (25 in Wuhan, 1 in Jingzhou, 1 in Ezhou, 3 in Xiaogan and 7 in Huanggang) .

In Wuhan, 24 died on the 27th, 25 on the 28th and 37 on the 29th.

I really hope this is the highest point.

Two Tangles in Wuhan

On the 29th, two things happened in Wuhan:

Dilemma 1: Is it the rumormonger or the ex Ante Zhuge Liang?

On December 31,2019, the Health Department of Wuhan City issued an information circular on the epidemic situation of pneumonia. Subsequently, a number of Internet users reported someone on the Internet to post false information. The Public Security Bureau has investigated and verified eight perpetrators. Education, criticism.

On the 28th, the Supreme People's Court newspaper commented on the case of "eight people being dealt with for spreading rumors" :

"As long as the information is basically true, the publishers and disseminators do not have malicious intentions and do not cause serious harm objectively, we should maintain a tolerant attitude towards such 'false information' . "

Wuhan Police issued a circular on the 29th saying that they had not given any warning, fine or detention.

Zeng Guang, chief scientist of epidemiology at the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said in a media interview on Thursday evening that the eight men were honorable and we can give them high marks in our comments afterwards; they were pre Zhuge Liang, but Science is about believing the evidence, making a judgment based on evidence.

The same thing, from a different angle to read the comments, there may be different answers. Either way, it taught us a lesson about the Internet.

Dilemma 2: SELL OR GIVE?

Shandong gave Wuhan 350 tons of vegetables as free aid, but the local Red Cross distributed them to major supermarkets, which sold them at slightly below market prices before handing over the money to the Red Cross, Shandong Lightning News reported.

The same is true of dishes from places such as Chongqing. All varieties of 2 yuan a catty, the dishes to the Red Cross. But, some Shandong Netizen, Wuhan Netizen does not buy, appeared on the net controversy.

A netizen suggests, gratuitously send community, give low income person, rich person goes buying food to eat.

This is really a "fair-minded and fair-minded and fair-minded" new problem. It is worth discussing from theory and practice afterwards, and even holding summit forum.

The Red Cross Society of Hubei, Hubei Charity Federation, Wuhan Charity Federation and Wuhan Red Cross charitable organizations have received about 3,995.46 million yuan in donations for the prevention and control of the epidemic. The Provincial Charity Federation has received about 1,248.55 million yuan in donations.

It is important to supervise the use of charitable funds and gifts.

Apologies are good medicine

At a press conference on the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic in Hubei Province on the evening of March 26, xiaodong Wang, the provincial governor, said on behalf of the provincial government: "after the outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia, the Party Central Committee and the people of the country worried, we felt very sad, very guilty, and very self-blame. "

On the evening of the 29th, at the same press conference, the governor made a bow to the "most beautiful retrograde person" -- The medical staff on the frontline. "since the outbreak of the epidemic, many friends have made criticisms, some of which are quite sharp. I understand that this is a bitter medicine for us, and they all hope that we will do a good job, " he said

The governor of Hubei Province bowed in honor of the medical staff

In the face of the unexpected events caused by human factors, the most effective way is to apologize first. At the same time, we will seriously review the loopholes in the work of relevant government departments and put forward effective measures as soon as possible to avoid more mistakes.

Since I am a new media person, I was invited to give a lecture on how officials deal with the media at a cadre training class at Wuhan University and other universities, in which I focused on the effectiveness of apologies.

I stress that in the Internet age, there are three main points that government officials should make when dealing with an emergency:

1. Must and can only tell the truth, and pay attention to the facts.

2. Zero rejections, and if possible, all the bad news at once.

3. Learn to apologize, lower expectations, and don't talk big.

2. Zero rejections, and if possible, all the bad news at once.

3. Learn to apologize, lower expectations, and don't talk big.

On September 14,2007, the executive meeting of the Shenzhen municipal government deliberated and adopted the interim measures of the Shenzhen municipal government departments on responsibility review and apology for dereliction of duty, it stipulates: "If a government department fails to perform or fails to perform its duties correctly, causing serious consequences or serious social impact, it shall apologize to the public. ". It's very forward-looking.

Hubei Province also has a tradition of valuing new media.

On the morning of January 7,2016, a seminar for representatives of the Internet sector in Hubei Province was held in Han. The then provincial Party secretary, Secretary General of the provincial Party Committee, Minister of the United Front Work Department, Minister of Propaganda Four Big Standing Committee, and 6 representatives of the network sector face-to-face exchange. I'm one of them. This is my first time in conference room one. The two-hour meeting went from 9:00 to 12:15. After finishing, the provincial Party secretary said: sorry, can not stay for dinner. You've taught us a lesson. Thank you.

Here, I would like to give the State Council client a proposal: The establishment of cadres at all levels to deal with the new media training courses. Making good use of new media is a very important quality of cadres.

I'm proud to be a journalist.

In March 2006, I attended the National People's Congress in Beijing. People's Daily online has invited 15 members of the member of the National People's Congress and the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference to open blogs. My blog is called "blog on behalf of Ye Qing. " . Write their own articles, their own revision, their posted online, why not! I write and send a single article every day. Unfortunately, in November 2019, the People's Daily online powerful nation blog was shut down.

Since March 2010, I have opened Weibo and Wechat, and now there are nine platforms, big and small.

I know how intellectuals should serve the people in the Internet age. I spend about two hours a day on the Internet. See the good article, after their own benefit, then send to everyone to see. It's well worth it. self-interest.

In May 2015, the central United Front Work Conference was held, with the united front target added to three categories: representatives of new media, returnees and new-generation entrepreneurs. At the end of November 2019, the central government convened a special United Front Work Conference for Internet personalities. From the national level, the proposed to give full play to the role of network personage signal.

I believe that the role of network personage will be played more. This "new type of pneumonia" period also illustrates this point.

The Doctor Sings "the story of Yueyang Tower"

On the main battlefield of Wuhan's battle against "new pneumonia" , moving things happen every day.

Wuhan First Hospital Deputy Director of gynecological Doctor Cao Lirong is the hospital's first batch of fighting, fall of the front-line doctors. On January 14, she developed symptoms and was quarantined at home with a high suspicion of COVID-19 pneumonia.

On the evening of the 28th, she heard Fan Zhongyan's story of Yueyang Tower on TV, and the more she heard it, the more it seemed to fit the mood of the medical staff. Usually she loves to sing, home sound effect is also good, decided to learn after recording to send to those who struggle in the front line comrades.

So, Cao Lirong recorded his a Cappella "Yueyang Tower, " to fight in the front of the comrades-in-arms refueling:

"When you live in a temple, you worry about your people. When you live far from the rivers and lakes, you worry about your king. When you go in, you worry about your king. When you go back, you worry about your king. "

She sang and listened to how many paramedics cried. And you can listen to it.

On December 31,2019, a patient with pneumonia of unknown cause was admitted to the infection department of People's Hospital of Wuhan University. On the same day, Director Gong Zujiong Infection Division in the morning session asked everyone to pay attention to personal protection. From January 7 to January 27,2020, a total of 75 patients who tested positive for COVID-19 and suspected to be infected were admitted to the department, the infection department, which has 148 medical staff, has not seen a single case of infection.

Protect yourself so you can help others.

We don't need another class dinner.

Six of the new cases, announced by the Hefei Municipal Health and Health Commission on January 29, were at the same party in Feidong County on January 21. One of them returned from Wuhan. We ate together, we were in the hospital together.

On the Internet, I saw a group of photos "medical staff sleeping position" : some medical staff lying on the floor, some in the armchair, hard to sleep. It's heartbreaking.

This is my second piece of advice today: Can I donate a foldout bed to a hospital?

Whatever is missing on the medical front, we will support. Don't you agree?

We need laughter in the House

On the 7th day of the "City closure" , Wuhan lights up a light show to cheer for the whole city.

Wuhan residents also suggested that at 8 pm on the 29th, residents of each district turn on their cell phone lights and do the district's light show. In the "new pneumonia" period, this is also a way to encourage each other. Just be careful, though.

Some community residents, began to make idiom on the mobile phone link the Dragon: One Heart, one mind..

In my circle of students, their teachers are playing tongue twisters:

Red Suit Red, yellow suit yellow, yellow suit no red suit red, red suit no yellow suit yellow.

And record it to see who's the best reader.

In fact, at this time, wechat group video is the best to use, as if in a video conference. Both at home and abroad.

Conclusion

After the Spring Festival, the temperature in Wuhan is higher and Higher Day by day.

What will China's economy look like in 2020? In 2003, China's economy totaled only 11 trillion yuan, but now it is more than 100 trillion yuan, and its capacity has been greatly enhanced.

China-thailand Securities Li Xunlei and other experts analysis that:

The main impact of the new crown outbreak on the Chinese economy is estimated to be in the range of one percentage point for the full year of tertiary sector of the economy.

From the time of impact, mainly in the first quarter. Because the first quarter's share of GDP was the smallest of the four quarters, the impact was relatively limited.
